casebody.data:
No. 2433. Ballew v. Anderson.

April Term, 1889.

May 20, 1889. B. W. Ball, for motion.

Order filed

per curiam,

Motion to reinstate appeal which had been dismissed by the clerk under'Rule 1. There had been a Case agreed upon, but such agreed Case was not filed within the time prescribed. Motion refused. Return, or agreed statement, must be filed within the time limited by the rules.
